From: "Yan, Zheng" <zheng.z.yan@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 15 Jun 2012 14:31:31 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 09/49] perf: Avoid race between cpu hotplug and installing
 event

upstream: fbfc623f8231c8d8c78aab5841e9c6e5811ab638

perf_event_open() requires the cpu on which to install event is online,
but the cpu can go offline after perf_event_open checks that. Add a
get_online_cpus()/put_online_cpus() pair to avoid the race.

Signed-off-by: Zheng Yan <zheng.z.yan@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra <a.p.zijlstra@chello.nl>
Link: http://lkml.kernel.org/r/1339741902-8449-3-git-send-email-zheng.z.yan@intel.com
Signed-off-by: Ingo Molnar <mingo@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Yunguo Wei <yunguo.wei@windriver.com>
---
 kernel/events/core.c |    5 +++++
 1 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/events/core.c b/kernel/events/core.c
index 184de95..4405f85 100644
--- a/kernel/events/core.c
+++ b/kernel/events/core.c
@@ -6259,6 +6259,8 @@ SYSCALL_DEFINE5(perf_event_open,
 		}
 	}
 
+	get_online_cpus();
+
 	event = perf_event_alloc(&attr, cpu, task, group_leader, NULL,
 				 NULL, NULL);
 	if (IS_ERR(event)) {
@@ -6397,6 +6399,8 @@ SYSCALL_DEFINE5(perf_event_open,
 	perf_unpin_context(ctx);
 	mutex_unlock(&ctx->mutex);
 
+	put_online_cpus();
+
 	event->owner = current;
 
 	mutex_lock(&current->perf_event_mutex);
@@ -6425,6 +6429,7 @@ err_context:
 err_alloc:
 	free_event(event);
 err_task:
+	put_online_cpus();
 	if (task)
 		put_task_struct(task);
 err_group_fd:
